RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 10500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2022 - 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE APRIL 16, 2022. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race at a mile or over since March 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming races for $ 4,000 or less not considered in eligibility and allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIDNIGHT BLUE NOTE moved forward and shifted in to set the pace inside but just off the rail while attended by an outside foe, was further engaged by that one coming to the midpoint of the far turn, dueled inside, drifted out gradually through the stretch bumping that rival lightly just past the eighth pole while edging away late. COSMIC TREASURE pressed from outside about three wide, forced the issue at the five-sixteenths, was carried out in the stretch and bumped lightly in the vicinity of the furlong grounds and was outfinished. NOT VERY GENTLE raced between rivals in the second flight two to three wide through the early going, began to drop back heading toward the far turn, swung eight wide for the stretch run and closed willingly to secure show honors. FORT RIDGE settled outside foes mid-pack three to four wide, continued well off the inside on the far turn in pursuit of the leading pair swinging five wide into upper stretch, ran on evenly and made no bid. IRISH MAJOR tracked from inside the second flight, came out a bit on the far turn before moving back in, ran evenly and made no bid. HONEST TO GOODNESS trailed racing near the inside and was not a factor. FOLLOWING AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF COSMIC TREASURE AGAINST MIDNIGHT BLUE NOTE ALLEGING INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH NO ACTION WAS TAKEN AND RESULTS TO STAND AS IS.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHIEF MYSTIQUE was forwardly-placed early chasing in behind the leaders, gradually dropped back three wide into and on the turn, swung out seven deep for the top of the stretch, rallied and surged past late. DURANGO CHROME broke awkwardly and slowly, steadily advanced three wide up the backstretch into the turn, came out a bit for the drive still advancing on the leaders, bid past the eighth pole, dueled and defeated the dueling partner but was outkicked by the aforementioned. STAN THE CAMERAMAN moved forward to duel inside a rival but off the rail, put that one away then faced a new outside challenger past the quarter pole, quickly dispatched that rival, lugged out a bit in mid-stretch and was engaged by yet another foe, was outfinished by that one and outkicked by the winner. CALICO JOE was bumped at the break, shifted in settling off the pace, came out to the three path leaving the turn, gained willingly in the lane. C F V NOBODYCARES switched off the inside, raced outside foes four deep into the turn, swung nine wide turning for home, kicked on mildly. SUPER CITRO appeared to false break then bumped a rival at the start, was encouraged forward pursuing the leaders three to four wide, made a swift advance leaving the turn to make a brief and mild bid at the top of the stretch, came in a bit in upper stretch and could not sustain the effort. LOOKING SALTY had the early lead under urging just briefly, steadily retreated. HOUR CAT forced the pace from outside, dueled three wide into the turn, faltered and faded.
